  "prompt": "Which organ is supplied with most blood.?",
  "response": "The organ that is supplied with the most blood is the lungs. The entire cardiac output from the right side of the heart is pumped to the lungs through the pulmonary artery, which branches into smaller arteries and capillaries to supply the lung tissue with blood for gas exchange. This is essential for oxygenating the blood before it is pumped to the rest of the body by the left side of the heart.",
